Looks more like a normal distribution here The more data, and more means, the more “normal” the histograms will look. BUT this can also hide the true distribution of the data so be sure to be careful.

summary(meanValues)
   Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
  11.30   16.42   18.65   17.96   19.41   23.77

Because these are already averages of counties –> the plots continue to look more normal. Summary statistics are “means of means”.
